videoTitle: At least 920 Florida teachers out of jobs after failing state test, despite 'effective' evaluations
videoDescription: At least 920 Florida teachers just received their pink slips and it's not because they can't teach, but because they can't pass a state ...
commentText: Being a teacher and that has taken the new version of this test, I can say this about the non-subjective sections of the test (which are all of them other than the essay) there is no problem with the academic material that is being tested. However, the time limits you are under for all sections of this test are completely ridiculous. As result from the time limits, if you are not a speed reader with very fast computational skills you will have a very hard time passing.                            As for the essay section I will say multiple problems exist.                                                       1. those that are hired to score the essays are not qualified and are simply following a formula given to them by their employer "Pearson" this formula dictates a score based off writing mechanisms rather than the actual content.  A big one of these would be the number of of transitions used in writing. It seems they are such a high importance that in fact It would most likely be a good idea to interrupt the flow of how the essay reads to include more transitions.                                                                2. Unless you can type over 30 words a minute you will not have enough time to type a passable essay.                                                              3. Considering the subject you will be typing about is completely random (will most likely have nothing to do with teaching or the educational field)and once again time limitations, unless you can type creatively on the fly with proper essay formatting you will not have enough time.  In regards to challenging your test results:                                              1. Don't bother on any of the academic sections (honestly as I said before there is nothing wrong with the questions the test asks as far as I could tell) it is just the limited time issue that is a problem.                                             2. As for the essay section, it can be challenged more successfully as it is subjective. (By their records the chance of successfully challenging is less than 2%)Honestly I failed the essay section 2 times while having passed the others on the first try.  I challenged both times because you are limited in the number of attempts you get to take the test per year.  The first time I challenged my score, I challenged on academic grounds using their own detailed guidelines on how the essay is graded to argue why I should have a better grade. I made more than a good argument and addressed each and every aspect of how the essay was supposedly grade.  The response I received was a cookie cutter letter saying they have decided the score is accurate. No reason given and the long argument I made was not addressed.There was little question after this that challenging a score on academic grounds valid or not was a waste of time.                                                                    3. The second time I took the essay I once again failed it (was not surprised by this as the essay I wrote the first time was better).  As explained above due to the limit on number of times you are allowed to take the test per year I challenged the score again. But this time successfully.  I am not going to give the exact details of how I managed this as it would invite others to use it for dishonest purposes. I will say though the challenge argument I used was based on the program used to give the essay portion of the test.  I pointed out a mechanism in the testing program that was extremely counter intuitive to the typical person and such cause unintended and unknown errors in what was typed by me the writer. I explained why the mechanism was not an excepted or expected occurrence and mentioned that no other word processing program in use whether it be a widely used program or not has such a mechanism.  I cited specific areas in my typed essay that suffered as result of the above mentioned mechanism.  As result of my argument based on the design of the testing program I received a letter about 7 weeks later simply saying that my test had been reviewed and it had been found that it may qualify for adjustment.  It did not say if the adjustment would mean I would now have a passing score which prompted a phone call to the FTCE customer service line.  When I spoke with the women on the phone she confirmed that the score had been changed to a PASS and she also mentioned I was the first person she ever talked to that managed to win a score verification challenge.  So in short if you plan on challenging your test results you will have to write a extremely detailed argument essay that in itself would easily pass if being scored (this time you should have a good idea what you will be typing about beforehand).  Challenging your score based on academics is futile and the only chance you have to succeed is to attack how the test is being given.                                                                                         So as for the question should the test be changed and how.The answer is yes, but the content of the test is just fine.  I also do not believe that the government throwing money at people or paying for test retakes will serve well.                 Change the following:                                  1. The amount of time given on all sections should be increased a good amount.  Really the test should be about if you can answer the questions effectively not a test of speed.                                                    2. If you pay to challenge your test score you should receive and retain detailed report showing why you did not pass especially on subjective sections.  This report should be detailed enough that a person would easily became to understand what they need to work on/learn in order to pass the test the next time.                                                       3.  Especially for the subjective area of the test (essay section) another company that has no conflicts of interests should be used to grade the test.   Honestly it is in the interest of "Pearson" for you to fail the test, so having them grade the test especially the sections where they will be grade subjectively is a conflict of interest that should not exist.
